S|# 20 · Trend Radar · Isaac (Knowledge)|> **Isaac** identifies trends across the workspaces — research/trend analysis that feeds dec-making and especially cnt creation across all soc platforms.
S|Purpose|"Isaac is identifying trends across your workspaces." A research and trend-analysis feed that surfaces what's moving in the owner's spaces, feeding into **dec-making** and **cnt creation** ideas for every soc platform.
S|What it covers (stated + inferred)|- **Trend detection** across workspaces — emerging topics, formats, and demand signals relevant to the owner's businesses. // - **Research/trend analysis cards** that feed: //   - **cnt** — cnt ideas for all soc platforms (links into cnt pl / Short pl / soc Approvals). //   - **dec-making** — strategic inputs that can flow to the Advisory Council and dec Queue (e.g. the "is agt-as-a-service real demand?" research seen in the mem Library is the kind of analysis Isaac produces). // - Likely tagged
S|Agent & relationships|- **Isaac** is the trend/research agt (a Workspace-tier master in the Org Chart). // - Outputs feed **Brain & Wiki** (as research mem), **cnt pl / Idea Feed** (as ideas), and **Advisory Council** (as strategic input). // > **Confidence:** Named and described in the walkthrough and present in the sidebar (knw section), but not shown as a dedicated full screen. The card/feed structure above is *inferred* from its description and from the research-note format visible in the mem Library.